Executive Profile
Richard J. Meelia  Chief Executive Officer, Tyco Healthcare Retail Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships68--
Background

		Mr. Richard J. Meelia, also known as Rich, serves as a Principal of Meelia Ventures, LLC. Mr. Meelia has been Executive Officer of Power Medical Interventions, Inc. since September 2009. He serves as Associate of Kairos Partners L.P. He served as the President of Infusaid, Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Covidien Ltd. from January 2006 to July 1, 2011. He served as the President of Covidien Inc. from 1995 to July 1, 2011. From July 2007 ... to July 2011, he served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Covidien plc. From January 1991 to January 1995, Mr. Meelia served as the Group President of Kendall Healthcare Products Company. He served as Chief Executive Officer at Tyco Healthcare Retail Group, Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Tyco Healthcare since June 2006 and President of Tyco Healthcare and Specialty Product of Tyco International Ltd. since 1995. He served as Chairman of Covidien Plc, Chief Executive Officer of Covidien Plc and President of Covidien Plc at Nellcor Puritan Bennett LLC. He served as Vice President of Tyco International Ltd. since June 2000. He has been the Chairman of Haemonetics Corporation since June 3, 2011 and its Independent Director since June 3, 2016. He serves as Chairman of Apollo Endosurgery, Inc. and has been its Director since July 2012. He serves as a Director of Triangle, Inc. He has been a Director of ConforMIS, Inc. since June 2015. He serves as a Director of Mallinckrodt LLC. He also serves on the Board of Governors of the Tufts-New England Medical Center and the Board of Trustees of St. Anselm College. He is member of several charitable boards, including Tufts Medical Center. He served as the Chairman of Covidien Plc from October 2008 to March 13, 2012. He served as a Director of Aspect Medical Systems, Inc. from 2001 to September 23, 2005. He served as a Director of VASAMED, Inc. since June 1997 and Covidien plc since June 2007. He served as an Independent Director of Haemonetics Corporation from July 27, 2005 to 2008. He has a Bachelor's Degree from Saint Anselm College. Mr. Meelia earned an MBA degree from Boston College.Read Full Background




