This event has passed.
The Covidien Story: Commitment to Innovation, New Ideas and Technology

December 8, 2010 at  6:00 PM - 9:00 PM $45




Event Navigation

« Concept Clinic with Oxalys Pharmaceuticals
Near Field Communication (NFC): The RFID Revolution for your Mobile Phone — e-Wallets and much more »








Featuring  Richard J. Meelia, Chairman, President and CEO, Covidien
For Covidien, it’s a new era with nothing but promise. After separating from Tyco International in 2007, Covidien is now a $10 billion, 43,000 employee global healthcare products leader dedicated to innovation and long-term growth.
How has Covidien reached these new heights? CEO Richard Meelia will share his story on how this Massachusetts based company has become a market leader through increased research and development, targeted acquisitions and an enhanced global infrastructure, including sales, marketing and distribution.
Following Richard Meelia there will be a medtech investor panel discussing start-up strategies and the potential acquisition by companies like Covidien.
•	Is the end-game strategy of acquisition a good idea for medtech companies?
•	What are large medtech companies seeking in an acquisition?
•	How can entrepreneurs best prepare, promote and position their technology for an acquisition strategy?
Panelists:
John L. Brooks,  CEO of Reflectance Medical, a noninvasive tissue perfusion company.
John also manages Healthcare Capital Consulting LLC, an advisory services and consulting firm that consults with life science companies, especially early stage start-ups that are seeking strategic advice as well as access to capital to initiate, develop and grow their businesses.
Ed Cahill, Partner, HLM Venture Partners, which provides venture capital to emerging companies focused on health care information technology, health care services and medical devices.
Jed Cohen, Managing Director, Investment Banking, Medical Devices of Leerink Swann, an investment bank to both emerging and established healthcare companies.
 Jonathan (Johnny) Reis, Founder & Managing Partner of Extera Partners, a global life sciences management firm that specializes in corporate and business development, product commercialization in Europe and the US, and company turnarounds.
Moderated by:
Richard 							B. 							Smith, Partner, Edwards Angell Palmer & Dodge
Rich counsels medtech companies on corporate issues including mergers and acquisitions, corporate formation, venture capital and other financing, joint ventures, university licensing and intellectual property strategies.


